                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-06T22:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 6, 1937—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 6—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>251. My 250, August 6, 9 p.m. The British Chargé d’Affaires has not yet received
                    from London a request for his opinion and comment concerning the proposal of his
                    Government to extend good offices in <pb facs="0349" n="342" xml:id="pg_342"/>
                    the Sino-Japanese conflict. In view of the Department’s 138, August 5, noon,
                    however, he will probably cable his opinion to London tomorrow. He states that
                    he fully agrees with my views as to the best method of approach but believes
                    that an early clash between the opposing forces is unlikely and that any
                    proposal of good offices had better be made somewhat later after the adjournment
                    of the Diet. He will inform me tomorrow of the nature of his recommendations to
                    his Government which I shall then cable to the Department together with my
                    comment thereon.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
